===2020 census===
The [[2020 United States census]] counted 251 people, 124 households, and 98 families in Camp Sherman.<ref>{{Cite web |title=US Census Bureau, Table P16: HOUSEHOLD TYPE |url=https://data.census.gov/table?q=Camp%20Sherman%20CDP,%20Oregon%20p16&y=2020 |access-date=January 5, 2025 |website=data.census.gov}}</ref><ref name="Census2020_DP1" /> The population density was 79.7 per square mile (30.8/km{{sup|2}}). There were 373 housing units at an average density of 118.4 per square mile (45.7/km{{sup|2}}).<ref name="Census2020_DP1">{{Cite web |title=US Census Bureau, Table DP1: PROFILE OF GENERAL POPULATION AND HOUSING CHARACTERISTICS |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDP2020.DP1?q=Camp%20Sherman%20CDP,%20Oregon%20dp1 |access-date=January 5, 2025 |website=data.census.gov}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Gazetteer Files |url=https://www.census.gov/geographies/reference-files/2020/geo/gazetteer-file.html |access-date=December 30, 2023 |website=Census.gov |publisher=United States Census Bureau}}</ref> The racial makeup was 91.63% (230) [[White (U.S. Census)|white]] or [[European American|European American]] (89.64% [[Non-Hispanic White|non-Hispanic white]]), 0.0% (0) [[African American (U.S. Census)|black]] or [[African American|African-American]], 1.2% (3) [[Native American (U.S. Census)|Native American]] or [[Alaska Native|Alaska Native]], 0.4% (1) [[Asian (U.S. Census)|Asian]], 0.0% (0) [[Pacific Islander (U.S. Census)|Pacific Islander]] or [[Native Hawaiian|Native Hawaiian]], 0.0% (0) from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 6.77% (17) from [[Multiracial Americans|two or more races]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=US Census Bureau, Table P1: RACE |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALPL2020.P1?q=Camp%20Sherman%20CDP,%20Oregon%20p1&y=2020 |access-date=January 5, 2025 |website=data.census.gov}}</ref> [[Hispanic (U.S. Census)|Hispanic]] or [[Latino (U.S. Census)|Latino]] of any race was 5.18% (13) of the population.<ref>{{Cite web |title=US Census Bureau, Table P2: HISPANIC OR LATINO, AND NOT HISPANIC OR LATINO BY RACE |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALPL2020.P2?q=Camp%20Sherman%20CDP,%20Oregon%20p2&y=2020 |access-date=January 5, 2025 |website=data.census.gov}}</ref>

Of the 124 households, 22.6% had children under the age of 18; 66.9% were married couples living together; 12.1% had a female householder with no spouse or partner present. 18.5% of households consisted of individuals and 8.1% had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older.<ref name="Census2020_DP1" /> The average household size was 2.8 and the average family size was 3.1.<ref>{{Cite web |title=US Census Bureau, Table S1101: HOUSEHOLDS AND FAMILIES |url=https://data.census.gov/table/ACSST5Y2020.S1101?q=Camp%20Sherman%20CDP,%20Oregon%20s1101%20&y=2020 |access-date=January 5, 2025 |website=data.census.gov}}</ref> The percent of those with a bachelor’s degree or higher was estimated to be 53.8% of the population.<ref>{{Cite web |title=US Census Bureau, Table S1501: EDUCATIONAL ATTAINMENT |url=https://data.census.gov/table/ACSST5Y2020.S1501?q=Camp%20Sherman%20CDP,%20Oregon%20s1501%20&y=2020 |access-date=January 5, 2025 |website=data.census.gov}}</ref>

11.2% of the population was under the age of 18, 2.0% from 18 to 24, 14.7% from 25 to 44, 31.9% from 45 to 64, and 40.2% who were 65 years of age or older. The median age was 63.1 years. For every 100 females, there were 88.7 males.<ref name="Census2020_DP1" /> For every 100 females ages 18 and older, there were 97.3 males.<ref name="Census2020_DP1" />

The 2016-2020 5-year [[American Community Survey|American Community Survey]] estimates show that the median household income was $77,917 (with a margin of error of +/- $18,397). The median family income was $95,625 (+/- $45,396).<ref>{{Cite web |title=US Census Bureau, Table S1903: MEDIAN INCOME IN THE PAST 12 MONTHS (IN 2020 INFLATION-ADJUSTED DOLLARS) |url=https://data.census.gov/table/ACSST5Y2020.S1903?q=Camp%20Sherman%20CDP,%20Oregon%20s1903%20&y=2020 |access-date=January 5, 2025 |website=data.census.gov}}</ref> Males had a median income of $47,500 (+/- $14,022) versus $36,875 (+/- $13,568) for females. The median income for those above 16 years old was $39,792 (+/- $16,458).<ref>{{Cite web |title=US Census Bureau, Table S2001: EARNINGS IN THE PAST 12 MONTHS (IN 2020 INFLATION-ADJUSTED DOLLARS) |url=https://data.census.gov/table/ACSST5Y2020.S2001?q=Camp%20Sherman%20CDP,%20Oregon%20s2001%20&y=2020 |access-date=January 5, 2025 |website=data.census.gov}}</ref> Approximately, 0.0% of the population were below the [[poverty line]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=US Census Bureau, Table S1701: POVERTY STATUS IN THE PAST 12 MONTHS |url=https://data.census.gov/table/ACSST5Y2020.S1701?q=Camp%20Sherman%20CDP,%20Oregon%20s1701%20&y=2020 |access-date=January 5, 2025 |website=data.census.gov}}</ref>

